ors and Authoritian Rulers of Southeast Europe\n  | publisher = Purdue University Press\n  | isbn = 978-1-55753-455-2\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Goldstein\n  | first = Ivo\n  | author-link = Ivo Goldstein\n  | title = Croatia: A History\n  | publisher = C. Hurst & Co.\n  | location = London\n  | year = 1999\n  | isbn = 978-1-85065-525-1\n  | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=pSxJdE4MYo4C&printsec=frontcover\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Hoare\n  | first = Marko Attila\n  | authorlink = Marko Attila Hoare\n  | contribution = Civilian-Military Relations in Bosnia-Herzegovina 1992\u20131995\n  | editor-last1 = Maga\u0161\n  | editor-first1 = Branka\n  | editor-last2 = \u017dani\u0107\n  | editor-first2 = Ivo\n  | title = The War in Croatia and Bosnia-Herzegovina 1991\u20131995\n  | pages = 178\u2013199\n  | year = 2001\n  | publisher = Frank Cass\n  | location = London\n  | isbn = 978-0-7146-8201-3\n  | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=9NljlSh2vpIC&printsec=frontcover\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Hoare\n  | first = Marko Attila\n  | year = 2006\n  | title = Genocide and Resistance in Hitler's Bosnia: The Partisans and the Chetniks 1941\u20131943\n  | publisher = Oxford University Press\n  | location = New York\n  | isbn = 978-0-19-726380-8\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Hoare\n  | first = Marko Attila\n  | year = 2007\n  | title = The History of Bosnia: From the Middle Ages to the Present Day\n  | publisher = Saqi\n  | location = London\n  | isbn = 978-0-86356-953-1\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Hoare\n  | first = Marko Attila\n  | year = 2013\n  | title = Bosnian Muslims in the Second World War\n  | publisher = Oxford University Press\n  | location = Oxford, UK\n  | isbn = 978-0-231-70394-9\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Hockenos\n  | first = Paul\n  | year = 2003\n  | title = Homeland Calling: Exile Patriotism and the Balkan Wars\n  | publi